texts.text: >Somewhere in the city...
Is it up here, leader?
Yes. That evil energy is flowing towards this point.
If we can save this site, most of the darkness engulfing Tokyo should dissipate.
Leader, look!
>From deep within the darkness, a demon looks on from above the site.
Wait... Was it always that big?
It's enormous... And grotesque...!
B-Baldur!
Please extinguish that creature with your brilliance!
Bring peace unto this world once more with your light...!
Humans, you must leave this place at once.
What...?
>The demon begins to shake violently!
>It spawns an even thicker darkness and heads towards the worshippers!
>They can't escape...!
*Scream*
What...? What the hell was that?!
I can't see anything. It's completely dark...!
Everyone, please calm down!
We have Baldur on our side.
He will surely cleanse this darkness with his power...!
Yes. Believe in the light. Believe in Baldur!
We are protected by Baldur, the guardian of light...!
Wait... Is that...?
>A faint glimmer of light appears in deep within the darkness.
Hey, it's...!
It must be Baldur! We must go! To the source of the light!
>The worshippers make their way towards the light.
>It grows brighter as they approach.
...?! It that...?
*Scream*
*Roar*
Everyone here?!
Don't stray too far. If you get lost, that's it!
How?! We can hardly tell friend from foe apart!
Is that... The Liberators?
They were here too.
Even though they are powerless, they risk their lives in this darkness.
Why...? They are but ordinary humans.
They do not possess Baldur's magnificent radiance...
Unless they have acquired the light to battle against this darkness...?
Everyone. We must aid the Liberators.
But how can we in this darkness.
We must do what we can!
How can be possibly help them...?
Liberators...! Can you hear me?!
...!! The leader?!
We are here to aid you!
But we have no means of defeating these demons...
Is there anything we can do to help?!
There is one thing I want to try.
I have no idea what's going to happen,
but can you try and hold these demons off?
Hold them off... It may not be enough, but we can put up a barrier.
Everyone, form up and stay together.
Get the demons to focus on us. Don't let them near the worshippers!
What do plan on doing, Shiori?!
Those unkillable demons.
I watched that video over and over again and figured out something.
They're not unkillable. They're just reviving ridiculously fast.
They disappear like they've been beaten,
but they actually aren't.
They recover by absorbing the darkness around them... And come back to life.
How's that possible?!
I don't know how, but they are so it is!
With the demons in Seiran's video, the darkness wasn't nearly as thick.
It took those demons 7.8 seconds to make their recovery.
In this stuff, it's been around 2 or 3 seconds.
In a way, the thicker the darkness, the faster they recover.
Even if it looks like they've been defeated, keep attacking.
That or...
I see. That's why you need them to help. So we don't miss our chance.
But I have no idea if this is actually going to work.
Nonetheless, we have no time to test this out.
If Shionyan says so, then I'll do so!
Good. Do it!
Yes, ma'am!
Let's try it!
Yes, ma'am!
I'll join too!
Shionyan's a genius, so things should work out!
We are ready... Activating the circle!
>A magic circle emits a faint light as it appears in the darkness...!
The demons... There!!
*Gasp*
Got it cornered! Where's our backup?!
*Shriek*
It's working!
Liberators! Fire at will!
Hit it with everything!
Copy!
*Roar*
>The Liberators attack the demon with their full fury...!
*Groan*
How's that...?!
>The demon falls to the ground on top of the circle...
>The fails to recover.
We... We did it!!
See, I'm a genius.
We... We did that? We defeated a demon?
That's hardly the end of it.
Yeah. There's more where that came from.
And we can't really retreat either.
One more time! Just one more time!
I guess we have no choice...!
>Demons seem to slowly make their approach...
>Then...
I have born witness to your own brilliance.
This light...!
Baldur!
Ha!
There you are.
>The demon made of the darkness falls to Baldur's light.
Face my light and perish, foul creature who encroaches upon the land of these humans.
>The other demons also vanish as the light engulfs the darkness.
We had to work so hard just to get rid of one, but he did it all at once...
The great God of Light...
Yeah. I'm just glad he was on our side.
Praise Baldur!
This world is surely safe as long as we have Baldur with us!
But my time has come...
>Baldur's body begins to tremble and slowly disappear...!
But why?!
I knew this was meant to be...
I simply managed to slip away from the underworld for a brief moment.
I cannot be resurrected without Hel's acknowledgement. This was fated.
But Baldur...
This world will lose its light once more without you, Baldur.
Is this world doomed to destruction...?
The darkness that consumed your world this time.
And the bringer of death that it spawned and acted as the harbinger of this world's doom.
They have been vanquished, but whether this was a prelude to Ragnarok,
or the machinations of the malice borne by the humans of this world...
Not even we know the truth behind it.
However, we do know that this world is headed towards its own destruction.
Oh... But...
But ye humans have no need to despair.
You possess the light that will keep this destruction at bay.
What...?!
I have witnessed the light that humanity possesses.
That is what will be necessary to give yourselves a chance to fight this fate.
Even in my absence, the light will not be gone. Am I incorrect to say so, summoner?
Yes... It is as you say, oh radiant one.
This world depends upon the light we each bear within ourselves.
You graced us with your presence to tell us just that.
From the deep depths that are far beyond the reach of any light...
And it is time that I return there...
Humans, see the light, feel its radiance. Do not forget your love for the light.
I bestow my light upon thee.
>With that, Baldur quietly disappears...
I do not believe how we sought the help of a god,
or our choices thus far were mistaken in any way.
But Baldur has left us.
Leader...
Liberators.
Yes, leader?
I would like to hear more about you and your group.
We cannot squander the light that Baldur has bestowed upon us.
We must discover what actions we can take ourselves.
Of course.
Let's find it together. What we can do.
